	I hope everyone has as much fun playing this as I had
writing it.  It will run on any reasonably compatible PC, any
version of DOS.  It will also work on a monochrome screen.
	I wrote Solitaire about 3 years ago, with hopes of selling
it and I even went so far as to get it copywrited, but I have decided
to void the copywrite and release it for free.
	Solitaire is dependant on clock speed, and I took the time a
couple of years ago to take the PCjr into consideration, but faster
clock speeds may cause Solitaire to go a little too fast.
	If enough people are interested, I could post hacks for the
different dealys and colors so you can tailor it to your machine.
	Uuencoded executable follows:

